snippet: All three parties have vested interests in the Middle East peace process, leading analysts to say the current Kerry-led negotiations are inhibiting a final reckoning.
abstract: News analysis; breakdown in Middle East peace talks involve both Palestinians and Israelis balking on conditions set when American-brokered negotiations started in 2013; intense talks ensue in search of new set of conditions that might allow conversations to continue, even after Sec of State John Kerry says Washington will re-evaluate its role.
lead_paragraph: All three parties have vested interests in the Middle East peace process, leading analysts to say the current Kerry-led negotiations are inhibiting a final reckoning.

headline.main: A Peace Process in Which Process Has Come to Outweigh Peace
headline.print_headline: A Peace Process in Which Process Has Come to Outweigh Peace
